{"title_page": "Aegan", "text_new": "{{short description|2008 film by Raju Sundaram}}\n{{EngvarB|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Aegan\n| image          = Aegan Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Raju Sundaram]]\n| producer       = K. Karunamoorthy<br />[[C. Arunpandian]]\n| writer         = S. Ramakrishnan<br />Raju Sundaram<br /><small>'''(Dialogue)'''</small>\n| screenplay     = [[Raju Sundaram]]<br /><small>'''(Adapted Screenplay)'''</small><br />Farah Khan<br>Abbas Tyrewala<br>Rajesh Saathi<br /><small>'''(Original Screenplay)'''</small>\n| story          = [[Farah Khan]]<br /><small>'''(Original Story)'''</small><br />Raju Sundaram<br /><small>'''(Additional Story)'''</small>\n| based on       = {{Based on|''[[Main Hoon Na]]''|[[Farah Khan]]}}\n| starring       = [[Ajith Kumar]]<br />[[Nayanthara]]<br />[[Navdeep]]<br />[[Piaa Bajpai]]<br />[[Jayaram]]<br />[[Suman (actor)|Suman]]<br />[[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]]<br />[[Devan (actor)|Devan]]\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[Arjun Jena]]\n| editing        = [[V. T. Vijayan]]\n| studio         = [[Ayngaran International|Ayngaran International Films]]\n| distributor    = Ayngaran International\n| released       = 25 October 2008<ref name=\"girls\"/>\n| runtime        = 140 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''Aegan''''' ({{lang-ta|\u0b8f\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd}}) is a [[2008 in film|2008]] Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action film]] directed and co-written by [[Raju Sundaram]] and produced by [[Ayngaran International]]. It is based on the 2004 Indian film, ''[[Main Hoon Na]]''. It stars [[Ajith Kumar]] and [[Nayanthara]] in the lead roles, with [[Suman (actor)|Suman]], [[Jayaram]], [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]], [[Navdeep]], and [[Piaa Bajpai]] in supporting roles.\n\nThe film revolves around a daredevil cop who, on behalf of his ailing father and the ambition of a lieutenant general, returns to [[college]] in [[Ooty]]. Whilst protecting the general's daughter, he attempts to reconcile with his stepbrother from his father's marriage. Furthermore, he has to ward off the international criminal John Chinnappa, who is trying to kill the general, an ex-aide of his who has turned police approver. How the cop manages to solve all three problems forms the crux of the story.\n\nThe film opened to Indian audiences on 25 October 2008, coinciding with the [[Diwali]] season. The film, upon release received mixed reviews and did good business at box office. The film was later dubbed into [[Hindi]] as ''Jaanbaaz Commando'' in 2012.\n\n== Plot ==\n''Aegan'''s story is based around Shiva ([[Ajith Kumar]]), a [[Criminal Investigation Department (India)|CB-CID]] officer, and his efforts to foil the terrorist John Chinnappa ([[Suman (actor)|Suman]]). Shiva is simultaneously attempting to mend relations with his father's estranged first wife and his half-brother Narain ([[Navdeep]]). However, complications ensue.\n\nMajor John Chinnappa is a scientist who had created tablets by operating on human [[guinea pig]]s. His ploys have always been [[controversy|controversial]] but inconclusive due to the lack of witnesses. However, an ex-gang member, General Ram Prasad ([[Devan (actor)|Devan]]), became a [[Informant|police approver]] and is on the verge of revealing John's ploys to the police. However, he is on the run to avoid charges. The case falls to [[Police Commissioner|Commissioner]] Karthikeyan ([[Nassar]]), Shiva's father, who assigns his son to go and help solve the mission.\n\nKarthik tells Shiva to attend college in [[Tamil Nadu]] \u2013 St. John's College, [[Ooty]] \u2013 to protect Ram's daughter, Pooja ([[Piaa Bajpai]]), from meeting with her father. Shiva pleads that he has never undertaken this type of a mission before and does not know much about the current generation. The general points out that, by a strange coincidence, Pooja attends school in the same town where Ram is hiding. Shiva can protect Pooja and look for Ram at the same time. Shiva goes undercover as a student returning to college after many years away taking care of the family business. He is much older than the other students, who at first make fun of him because of his lack of new-generation styles. He also has to deal with the many goofy teachers as well the idiotic forgetful principal of the college, Albert ([[Jayaram]]).\n\nShiva finds Narain, who is later revealed to be his brother. Pooja is Narain's best friend, and he is secretly jealous that other girls can get his attention, but she cannot. Shiva saves Pooja from John's men, who kidnap her, while Narain and others think that it is a prank. He later becomes a sensation among the students and teachers. He befriends Narain and Pooja and falls in love with the [[chemistry]] teacher, Mallika ([[Nayanthara]]), after being attracted by her beauty and in a bid to convince other students that he is one of them. During his regular [[jogging]], sessions Shiva spots Ram and chases him until he escapes with the help of an [[helmet]]-clad bike rider, who is later revealed to be Narain. Pooja comes to know that Narain has been helping her father and feels cheated by him.\n\nNarain tries to apologise to Pooja many times, but she refuses to talk to him. Irked by this, Narain drinks and explains his actions when John's men come again to kidnap Pooja. They beat up Narain, but Shiva comes to their rescue. Narain and Pooja patch up after the fight sequences. Shiva takes Narain to his home, where he learns that Narain is his brother and meets his mother Kasthuri ([[Suhasini]]). The flashback sequences describe Shiva's childhood (he is an orphan) and explain why his mother and father live separately.\n\nThe next day, when Pooja introduces Ram to Shiva, Shiva arrests him \u2013 much to the disappointment of Pooja and Narain. Then everyone in the college, including Mallika, learns that Shiva is a policeman. Shiva then drives Ram straight to John's hiding place, avoiding the traps that he had set. A fight ensues between Shiva and John's men in which John is finally killed.\n\nIn the final scenes, Mallika is shown with Shiva's parents and brother, while Shiva has gone to [[Afghanistan]] as part of another mission.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Ajith Kumar]] as Shiva, CB-CID officer  \n* [[Nayanthara]] as Mallika, chemistry teacher\n* [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Karthikeyan, Shiva's foster father\n* [[Jayaram]] as Albert Aadiyapatham, the college principal\n* [[Suman (actor)|Suman]] as John Chinnappa, a scientist and terrorist\n* [[Navdeep]] as Narain, Shiva's brother\n* [[Piaa Bajpai]] as Pooja, Narain's love interest\n* [[Devan (actor)|Devan]] as Ram Prasad, Pooja's father\n* [[Suhasini]] as Kasthuri, Shiva's foster mother\n* [[Cochin Hanifa]] as Hanifa\n* [[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]] as Kamalakannan, professor\n* [[Sathyan Sivakumar|Sathyan]] as Mani, college peon\n* [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]] as John's bodyguard\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nIn September 2007, early indications suggested that [[Ayngaran International]] were set to make a film starring [[Ajith Kumar]] directed by [[Venkat Prabhu]],<ref name=\"vpn\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Venkat Prabhu directs Ajith|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=29 February 2008|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/36922.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080303000627/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/36922.html| archivedate= 3 March 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> however the chance went to first-time director [[Raju Sundaram]], in a project titled ''Akbar''.<ref name=\"akbar\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Ajith's Akbar eyes Parvathi|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=18 October 2007|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/oct-07-03/18-10-07-akbar.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071020031740/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/oct-07-03/18-10-07-akbar.html| archivedate= 20 October 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> Despite denying the title, Ajith confirmed the project and stating that he had put on weight and grew a beard for his participation in the project. Following the success of ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]'', \"Thala\" Ajith Kumar waited till the birth of his first child, in January 2008, before commencing his shoot for the film.\n\nThe 40-member unit consisting of \"Thala\" Ajith, director Raju Sundaram, cinematographer [[Arjun Jena]], action choreographer [[Stun Siva]] and a few stunt men from Chennai flew to Hong Kong on 14 January 2008 and began their first schedule for a 10-day stint.<ref name=\"honkonga\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajith to fly to Hong Kong|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=14 January 2008|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35893.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115175508/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35893.html| archivedate= 15 January 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nThe portions in Hong Kong were shot showing \"Thala\" Ajith's introduction stunt scene set against the skyscrapers, [[Hong Kong airport]], and the sea with the help of Chinese action choreographers. The crew shot schedules in [[Theni]] and [[Ooty]] and other locations in [[South India]] during the filming. The film finished its talkie portion in early September 2008, and the songs were canned in [[India]] as well as parts of [[Switzerland]].<ref name=\"ree\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Aegan in Chennai Central |publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=4 September 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-08-01/aegan-04-09-08.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080906211146/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-08-01/aegan-04-09-08.html| archivedate= 6 September 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"arun\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajit is Aegan!|publisher=Sify|accessdate=26 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14610525| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080302005750/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14610525| archivedate= 2 March 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"remake\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajit next film- 'Mein Hoon Naa'?|publisher=Sify|accessdate=1 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14598581| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080206064941/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14598581| archivedate= 6 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> The film, initially described as a \"musical action comedy,\". The film previously referred to as ''Akbar'', ''Ramakrishnan'' and ''Anthony Gonsalves''<ref name=\"remake\"/> was christened as ''Aegan'', a name of [[Shiva]].\n\n=== Casting ===\nFollowing the announcement of the project, tentatively titled as ''Akbar'', [[Shriya Saran]] was rumoured to be the heroine, following her successful role in ''[[Sivaji: The Boss]]''. However, due to differences, Saran was ousted from the project due to her limited callsheets, as she had to fly to and from [[United States|America]] where she was then shooting for her Hollywood film, ''[[The Other End of the Line]]''. However other indications claimed that Saran was ousted from the project due to her involvement in ''[[Indiralohathil Na Azhagappan]]'', in which she appeared in an [[item number]], which [[Ajith Kumar]] was unhappy with due to previous feuds with the lead, [[Vadivelu]] of that film.<ref name=\"vadivelu\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Shriya lost the chance but Cool|publisher=Dailomo.com|accessdate=7 December 2007|url=http://www.dailomo.com/tamil/articles/174/1/Shriya-lost-the-chance-but-Cool/Page1.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212225943/http://www.dailomo.com/tamil/articles/174/1/Shriya-lost-the-chance-but-Cool/Page1.html|archivedate=12 December 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref> Reports indicated that [[Parvati Melton]] had replaced Saran but later denied it signalling that she was not approached.<ref name=\"akbar\"/>\n\n[[Suhani Kalita]] was announced as the second heroine of the project but was later removed for unknown reasons.<ref name=\"suhanr\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Billa now eyes Katrina|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=26 December 2007|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/dec-07-04/26-12-07-akbar.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071229042344/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/dec-07-04/26-12-07-akbar.html| archivedate= 29 December 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> Several [[Bollywood]] heroines including [[Deepika Padukone]],<ref name=\"deeps\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Ajith pairs with Deepika Padukone?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=17 November 2007|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/34710.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071118073411/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/34710.html| archivedate= 18 November 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Bipasha Basu]],<ref name=\"bips\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Bips to team up with Ajith!|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=11 January 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-08-02/11-01-08-bipasha-ajith.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115064832/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-08-02/11-01-08-bipasha-ajith.html| archivedate= 15 January 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Katrina Kaif]], [[Ayesha Takia]],<ref name=\"girls\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Shriya-Back as Ajit's heroine?|publisher=Sify|accessdate=10 January 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14587387| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115033656/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14587387| archivedate= 15 January 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Ileana D'Cruz]],<ref name=\"illy\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Is it Ileana?|publisher=Sify|accessdate=22 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609250| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080225115303/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609250| archivedate= 25 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Tanushree Dutta]]<ref name=\"tanu\">{{cite web|author=|year=2008|title=Ajith's Aegan (Tamil)|publisher=Eyakkam.com|accessdate=23 February 2008|url=http://i151.photobucket.com/albums/s160/ajith-fans-eyakkam/Feb08/feb22tm.jpg}}</ref>  and [[Sneha Ullal]]<ref name=\"girls\"/> were linked to the role, as well as reports that [[Shriya Saran]] would reprise the role after making up with Ajith.<ref name=\"girls\"/> The role eventually was given to [[Katrina Kaif]], who was set to make her debut in [[Tamil film]]s with ''Aegan'',<ref name=\"kat\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Welcome Katrina|publisher=Sify|accessdate=31 January 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14597870| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080201214606/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14597870| archivedate= 1 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> however she later opted out due to callsheet clashes.<ref name=\"katout\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Katrina opts out! |publisher=Sify|accessdate=16 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14605785| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080219074322/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14605785| archivedate= 19 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> It was announced that [[Nayantara]] would play the role of the heroine in the film, following her role opposite Ajith in ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]''.<ref name=\"nayt\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Nayan races ahead! |publisher=Sify|accessdate=24 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609765| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080226080009/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609765| archivedate= 26 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> In February 2008, it was confirmed that [[Navdeep]] would play a role in the film as well as [[Suman (actor)|Suman]], who will appear in a villainous role. [[Malayalam]] actor, [[Jayaram]] will also play a role in the film, which will be co-produced by actor, Arun Pandian.<ref name=\"arun\"/>\n\nNassar and [[Suhasini]] were selected to play the roles of the parents of [[Ajith Kumar|Ajith]],<ref name=\"parents\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajith's unnamed project touches French shores|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=9 February 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-01/09-02-08-ajith.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080212163942/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-01/09-02-08-ajith.html| archivedate= 12 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> whilst [[Raju Sundaram]]'s younger Brother, [[Prabhu Deva]] was given a chance to make a cameo appearance in the film as a dancer but politely refused.<ref name=\"deva\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Prabhu Deva dances with Ajith|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=6 December 2007|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35128.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071207093549/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35128.html| archivedate= 7 December 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> Supporting actors [[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]], Sathyan and Sriman also play roles in ''Aegan'', as does model [[Piaa Bajpai]], who appears as the ladylove to Navdeep.<ref name=\"bas\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Billa stars in new flick|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=27 February 2008|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/feb/27billa.htm| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080301234051/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/feb/27billa.htm| archivedate= 1 March 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"piya\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajith Changes|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=4 April 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-08-01/aegan-04-04-08.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080407111355/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-08-01/aegan-04-04-08.html| archivedate= 7 April 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Sivakarthikeyan]] and [[Arunraja Kamaraj]] shot for the film for one day as comedians portraying spies, but following changes to the script, their roles were removed.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-10/siva-karthikeyan-values-his-20-minutes-with-ajith-ajith-siva-karthikeyan-18-02-13.html</ref> [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] was signed on as the music composer whilst [[Arjun Jena]] was the cinematographer for the project<ref name=\"parents\"/> and Milan, who did the art direction for ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]'', renews his association with Ajith in the film.<ref name=\"milan\">{{cite web|year=2008|title= Ajith's Aegan takes a cue from Billa! |publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=16 February 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-02/16-02-08-aegan.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080221162755/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-02/16-02-08-aegan.html| archivedate= 21 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Aegan\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover      =\n| caption    = {{deletable image-caption|Thursday, 20 September 2018|PROD}}\n| alt        =\n| released   = 9 October 2008\n| recorded   = 2008\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 29:08\n| label      = Ayngaran Music<br />An Ak Audio<br/>[[Think Music India|Think Music]]\n| producer   = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title = [[Saroja (2008 film)#Soundtrack|Saroja]]\n| prev_year  = 2008\n| next_title = [[Silambattam (film)|Silambattam]]\n| next_year  = 2008\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack of ''Aegan'' was composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] as was the film score. It was noticeably, the third time Yuvan was scoring music for an [[Ajith Kumar]] film, after ''[[Dheena]]'' (2001) and ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]'' (2007), the songs of which had been very popular and went on to become chartbusters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/10023.html|title=Aegan \u2013 A Perfect Hat-Trick|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=5 August 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe soundtrack released on 9 October 2008,<ref name=\"musictracks\">{{cite web|author=|year=2008|title=Aegan \u2013 Official Audio Promo |publisher=[[Ayngaran International]]|accessdate=9 October 2008|url=http://www.ayngaran.com/newsdetails.php?newsid=106}}</ref> at a private ceremony at the [[Hello FM]] Studios by composer Yuvan Shankar Raja as the lead cast and the director were away shooting the video for the song in [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/2008/yuvan-aegan-audio-fm-station-131008.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120711224631/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/2008/yuvan-aegan-audio-fm-station-131008.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=11 July 2012 |title=Yuvan releases Aegan audio in FM station! |publisher=[[Oneindia]] |accessdate=5 August 2009 }}</ref> The album features 6 tracks overall, including one of the songs (\"Hey Salaa\") repeated at the end.\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra2 = [[Suvi Suresh]], Ujayinee, [[Sathyan (singer)|Sathyan]], [[Ranjith (Singer)|Ranjith]], [[Naveen]]\n| length10 = \n| total_length = 29:08\n| lyrics1 = [[Snehan]]\n| extra1 = [[Blaaze]], [[Naresh Iyer]], [[Mohammed Aslam]]\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| lyrics2 = [[Pa. Vijay]]\n| lyrics3 = Pa. Vijay\n| length9 = \n| extra3 = [[Shankar Mahadevan]]\n| lyrics4 = Snehan\n| extra4 = [[Krishna Kumar Kunnath]], [[Bela Shende]]\n| lyrics5 = Pa. Vijay\n| extra5 = [[Vasundhara Das]], [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| extra6 = \n| title10 = \n| title9 = \n| title1 = Hey Salaa\n| length4 = 4:31\n| length1 = 5:09\n| title2 = Yahoo Yahoo\n| length2 = 4:36\n| title3 = Hey Baby\n| length3 = 4:39\n| title4 = Odum Varayil\n| title5 = Kichu Kichu\n| length8 = \n| length5 = 5:11\n| title6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| lyrics6 = \n}}\n\n==Release==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Kalaignar TV|Kalaignar]]. The film was give a \"U\" certificate by the [[Indian Censor Board]], and was released during the Diwali weekend on 25 October 2008. The film was later dubbed in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Mallika I Love You''.<ref>http://www.ayngaran.com/frame.php?iframepath=newsdetails.php?newsid=1684</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n[[Sify]].com claimed that \"the trouble with the film is that it looks like an amateurish attempt by debutant director Raju Sundaram\" dismissing the [[Climax (narrative)|climax]] as \"a colossal embarrassment\", but adding that \"no film is perfect\". [[Ajith Kumar]] was praised for being \"at his best but look[ed] plump and stiff in some scenes where he need to be relaxed and natural\", drawing comparisons with a similar feedback from his previous venture, ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]''.<ref name=\"aeganreview\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Aegan|publisher=[[Sify]].com|accessdate=2008-10-25|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14784482&ctid=5&cid=2429| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081026050553/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14784482&ctid=5&cid=2429| archivedate= 26 October 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Nayanthara]] was said to \"look perfect as Mallika, a role that fits her like a glove\" with her make-up and costumes \"rocking\". The reviewer added that \"[[Piaa Bajpai]] is promising, Jayaram as Principal and Haneefa have been wasted and do little in the way of bringing smiles to the audiences faces\". The review also singles out the performance of rookie cinematographer, [[Arjun Jena]], whose work is labelled as \"eye-catching\".<ref name=\"aeganreview\"/>\n\nSimilarly [[Rediff]].com labelled the film as \"watchable in parts\", giving it negative feedback in comparison with ''[[Main Hoon Na]]''.<ref name=\"aeganreviewtwo\">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra|year=2008|title=Aegan is watchable in parts|publisher=[[Rediff]].com|accessdate=2008-10-25|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/oct/25aegan.htm}}</ref>  It like Sify, claims that \"Aegan loses its spontaneity and meanders between humour and seriousness\" in the second half. The reviewer praises Ajith claiming he looks as though he \"really did enjoy himself on screen, after a really long time\". The reviewer adds that \"Nayantara's outfits get smaller and smaller, while the actress herself has nothing more to do than dance in transparent saris and high-heels.<ref name=\"aeganreviewtwo\"/> Sometimes she looks amused, at others, irritated and bored\", comparing her unchallenging roles to previous roles in ''[[Sathyam (2008 film)|Sathyam]]'' and ''[[Kuselan]]''. It criticizes Piaa Bajpai claiming she \"hams it to glory\", and \"makes you want to watch [[Amrita Rao]]'s naivety in the original\", however, it praises [[Navdeep]] citing he is \"far more natural, but you pity the fact that his role is so small\". Rediff also criticized [[Suman (actor)|Suman]] and Sriman labelling their portrayals as \"pathetic\". In reference to minor characters, [[Cochin Hanifa]] is praised while [[Suhasini Mani Ratnam]]'s role is said to be \"terribly dealt with, robbing her part of any sympathy\".<ref name=\"aeganreviewtwo\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=1311638|title=Aegan}}\n\n[[Category:2008 films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:2000s action films]]\n[[Category:Tamil remakes of Hindi films]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Ooty]]\n[[Category:2000s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:2008 directorial debut films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2008 film by Raju Sundaram}}\n{{EngvarB|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Aegan\n| image          = Aegan Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Raju Sundaram]]\n| producer       = K. Karunamoorthy<br />[[C. Arunpandian]]\n| writer         = S. Ramakrishnan<br />Raju Sundaram<br /><small>'''(Dialogue)'''</small>\n| screenplay     = [[Raju Sundaram]]<br /><small>'''(Adapted Screenplay)'''</small><br />Farah Khan<br>Abbas Tyrewala<br>Rajesh Saathi<br /><small>'''(Original Screenplay)'''</small>\n| story          = [[Farah Khan]]<br /><small>'''(Original Story)'''</small><br />Raju Sundaram<br /><small>'''(Additional Story)'''</small>\n| based on       = {{Based on|''[[Main Hoon Na]]''|[[Farah Khan]]}}\n| starring       = [[Ajith Kumar]]<br />[[Nayanthara]]<br />[[Navdeep]]<br />[[Piaa Bajpai]]<br />[[Jayaram]]<br />[[Suman (actor)|Suman]]<br />[[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]]<br />[[Devan (actor)|Devan]]\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[Arjun Jena]]\n| editing        = [[V. T. Vijayan]]\n| studio         = [[Ayngaran International|Ayngaran International Films]]\n| distributor    = Ayngaran International\n| released       = 25 October 2008<ref name=\"girls\"/>\n| runtime        = 140 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''Aegan''''' ({{lang-ta|\u0b8f\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd}}) is a [[2008 in film|2008]] Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action film]] directed and co-written by [[Raju Sundaram]] and produced by [[Ayngaran International]]. It is based on the 2004 Indian film, ''[[Main Hoon Na]]''. It stars [[Ajith Kumar]] and [[Nayanthara]] in the lead roles, with [[Suman (actor)|Suman]], [[Jayaram]], [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]], [[Navdeep]], and [[Piaa Bajpai]] in supporting roles.\n\nThe film revolves around a daredevil cop who, on behalf of his ailing father and the ambition of a lieutenant general, returns to [[college]] in [[Ooty]]. Whilst protecting the general's daughter, he attempts to reconcile with his stepbrother from his father's marriage. Furthermore, he has to ward off the international criminal John Chinnappa, who is trying to kill the general, an ex-aide of his who has turned police approver. How the cop manages to solve all three problems forms the crux of the story.\n\nThe film opened to Indian audiences on 25 October 2008, coinciding with the [[Diwali]] season. The film, upon release received mixed reviews and did good business at box office. The film was later dubbed into [[Hindi]] as ''Jaanbaaz Commando'' in 2012.\n\n== Plot ==\n''Aegan'''s story is based around Shiva ([[Ajith Kumar]]), a [[Criminal Investigation Department (India)|CB-CID]] officer, and his efforts to foil the terrorist John Chinnappa ([[Suman (actor)|Suman]]). Shiva is simultaneously attempting to mend relations with his father's estranged first wife and his half-brother Narain ([[Navdeep]]). However, complications ensue.\n\nMajor John Chinnappa is a scientist who had created tablets by operating on human [[guinea pig]]s. His ploys have always been [[controversy|controversial]] but inconclusive due to the lack of witnesses. However, an ex-gang member, General Ram Prasad ([[Devan (actor)|Devan]]), became a [[Informant|police approver]] and is on the verge of revealing John's ploys to the police. However, he is on the run to avoid charges. The case falls to [[Police Commissioner|Commissioner]] Karthikeyan ([[Nassar]]), Shiva's father, who assigns his son to go and help solve the mission.\n\nKarthik tells Shiva to attend college in [[Tamil Nadu]] \u2013 St. John's College, [[Ooty]] \u2013 to protect Ram's daughter, Pooja ([[Piaa Bajpai]]), from meeting with her father. Shiva pleads that he has never undertaken this type of a mission before and does not know much about the current generation. The general points out that, by a strange coincidence, Pooja attends school in the same town where Ram is hiding. Shiva can protect Pooja and look for Ram at the same time. Shiva goes undercover as a student returning to college after many years away taking care of the family business. He is much older than the other students, who at first make fun of him because of his lack of new-generation styles. He also has to deal with the many goofy teachers as well the idiotic forgetful principal of the college, Albert ([[Jayaram]]).\n\nShiva finds Narain, who is later revealed to be his brother. Pooja is Narain's best friend, and he is secretly jealous that other girls can get his attention, but she cannot. Shiva saves Pooja from John's men, who kidnap her, while Narain and others think that it is a prank. He later becomes a sensation among the students and teachers. He befriends Narain and Pooja and falls in love with the [[chemistry]] teacher, Mallika ([[Nayanthara]]), after being attracted by her beauty and in a bid to convince other students that he is one of them. During his regular [[jogging]], sessions Shiva spots Ram and chases him until he escapes with the help of an [[helmet]]-clad bike rider, who is later revealed to be Narain. Pooja comes to know that Narain has been helping her father and feels cheated by him.\n\nNarain tries to apologise to Pooja many times, but she refuses to talk to him. Irked by this, Narain drinks and explains his actions when John's men come again to kidnap Pooja. They beat up Narain, but Shiva comes to their rescue. Narain and Pooja patch up after the fight sequences. Shiva takes Narain to his home, where he learns that Narain is his brother and meets his mother Kasthuri ([[Suhasini]]). The flashback sequences describe Shiva's childhood (he is an orphan) and explain why his mother and father live separately.\n\nThe next day, when Pooja introduces Ram to Shiva, Shiva arrests him \u2013 much to the disappointment of Pooja and Narain. Then everyone in the college, including Mallika, learns that Shiva is a policeman. Shiva then drives Ram straight to John's hiding place, avoiding the traps that he had set. A fight ensues between Shiva and John's men in which John is finally killed.\n\nIn the final scenes, Mallika is shown with Shiva's parents and brother, while Shiva has gone to [[Afghanistan]] as part of another mission.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Ajith Kumar]] as Shiva, CB-CID officer  \n* [[Nayanthara]] as Mallika, chemistry teacher\n* [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Karthikeyan, Shiva's foster father\n* [[Jayaram]] as Albert Aadiyapatham, the college principal\n* [[Suman (actor)|Suman]] as John Chinnappa, a scientist and terrorist\n* [[Navdeep]] as Narain, Shiva's brother\n* [[Piaa Bajpai]] as Pooja, Narain's love interest\n* [[Devan (actor)|Devan]] as Ram Prasad, Pooja's father\n* [[Suhasini]] as Kasthuri, Shiva's foster mother\n* [[Cochin Hanifa]] as Hanifa\n* [[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]] as Kamalakannan, professor\n* [[Sathyan Sivakumar|Sathyan]] as Mani, college peon\n* [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]] as John's bodyguard\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nIn September 2007, early indications suggested that [[Ayngaran International]] were set to make a film starring [[Ajith Kumar]] directed by [[Venkat Prabhu]],<ref name=\"vpn\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Venkat Prabhu directs Ajith|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=29 February 2008|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/36922.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080303000627/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/36922.html| archivedate= 3 March 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> however the chance went to first-time director [[Raju Sundaram]], in a project titled ''Akbar''.<ref name=\"akbar\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Ajith's Akbar eyes Parvathi|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=18 October 2007|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/oct-07-03/18-10-07-akbar.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071020031740/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/oct-07-03/18-10-07-akbar.html| archivedate= 20 October 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> Despite denying the title, Ajith confirmed the project and stating that he had put on weight and grew a beard for his participation in the project. Following the success of ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]'', \"Thala\" Ajith Kumar waited till the birth of his first child, in January 2008, before commencing his shoot for the film.\n\nThe 40-member unit consisting of \"Thala\" Ajith, director Raju Sundaram, cinematographer [[Arjun Jena]], action choreographer [[Stun Siva]] and a few stunt men from Chennai flew to Hong Kong on 14 January 2008 and began their first schedule for a 10-day stint.<ref name=\"honkonga\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajith to fly to Hong Kong|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=14 January 2008|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35893.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115175508/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35893.html| archivedate= 15 January 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nThe portions in Hong Kong were shot showing \"Thala\" Ajith's introduction stunt scene set against the skyscrapers, [[Hong Kong airport]], and the sea with the help of Chinese action choreographers. The crew shot schedules in [[Theni]] and [[Ooty]] and other locations in [[South India]] during the filming. The film finished its talkie portion in early September 2008, and the songs were canned in [[India]] as well as parts of [[Switzerland]].<ref name=\"ree\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Aegan in Chennai Central |publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=4 September 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-08-01/aegan-04-09-08.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080906211146/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-08-01/aegan-04-09-08.html| archivedate= 6 September 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"arun\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajit is Aegan!|publisher=Sify|accessdate=26 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14610525| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080302005750/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14610525| archivedate= 2 March 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"remake\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajit next film- 'Mein Hoon Naa'?|publisher=Sify|accessdate=1 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14598581| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080206064941/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14598581| archivedate= 6 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> The film, initially described as a \"musical action comedy,\". The film previously referred to as ''Akbar'', ''Ramakrishnan'' and ''Anthony Gonsalves''<ref name=\"remake\"/> was christened as ''Aegan'', a name of [[Lord Shiva]].\n\n=== Casting ===\nFollowing the announcement of the project, tentatively titled as ''Akbar'', [[Shriya Saran]] was rumoured to be the heroine, following her successful role in ''[[Sivaji: The Boss]]''. However, due to differences, Saran was ousted from the project due to her limited callsheets, as she had to fly to and from [[United States|America]] where she was then shooting for her Hollywood film, ''[[The Other End of the Line]]''. However other indications claimed that Saran was ousted from the project due to her involvement in ''[[Indiralohathil Na Azhagappan]]'', in which she appeared in an [[item number]], which [[Ajith Kumar]] was unhappy with due to previous feuds with the lead, [[Vadivelu]] of that film.<ref name=\"vadivelu\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Shriya lost the chance but Cool|publisher=Dailomo.com|accessdate=7 December 2007|url=http://www.dailomo.com/tamil/articles/174/1/Shriya-lost-the-chance-but-Cool/Page1.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212225943/http://www.dailomo.com/tamil/articles/174/1/Shriya-lost-the-chance-but-Cool/Page1.html|archivedate=12 December 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref> Reports indicated that [[Parvati Melton]] had replaced Saran but later denied it signalling that she was not approached.<ref name=\"akbar\"/>\n\n[[Suhani Kalita]] was announced as the second heroine of the project but was later removed for unknown reasons.<ref name=\"suhanr\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Billa now eyes Katrina|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=26 December 2007|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/dec-07-04/26-12-07-akbar.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071229042344/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/dec-07-04/26-12-07-akbar.html| archivedate= 29 December 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> Several [[Bollywood]] heroines including [[Deepika Padukone]],<ref name=\"deeps\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Ajith pairs with Deepika Padukone?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=17 November 2007|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/34710.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071118073411/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/34710.html| archivedate= 18 November 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Bipasha Basu]],<ref name=\"bips\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Bips to team up with Ajith!|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=11 January 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-08-02/11-01-08-bipasha-ajith.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115064832/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-08-02/11-01-08-bipasha-ajith.html| archivedate= 15 January 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Katrina Kaif]], [[Ayesha Takia]],<ref name=\"girls\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Shriya-Back as Ajit's heroine?|publisher=Sify|accessdate=10 January 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14587387| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115033656/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14587387| archivedate= 15 January 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Ileana D'Cruz]],<ref name=\"illy\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Is it Ileana?|publisher=Sify|accessdate=22 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609250| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080225115303/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609250| archivedate= 25 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Tanushree Dutta]]<ref name=\"tanu\">{{cite web|author=|year=2008|title=Ajith's Aegan (Tamil)|publisher=Eyakkam.com|accessdate=23 February 2008|url=http://i151.photobucket.com/albums/s160/ajith-fans-eyakkam/Feb08/feb22tm.jpg}}</ref>  and [[Sneha Ullal]]<ref name=\"girls\"/> were linked to the role, as well as reports that [[Shriya Saran]] would reprise the role after making up with Ajith.<ref name=\"girls\"/> The role eventually was given to [[Katrina Kaif]], who was set to make her debut in [[Tamil film]]s with ''Aegan'',<ref name=\"kat\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Welcome Katrina|publisher=Sify|accessdate=31 January 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14597870| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080201214606/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14597870| archivedate= 1 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> however she later opted out due to callsheet clashes.<ref name=\"katout\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Katrina opts out! |publisher=Sify|accessdate=16 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14605785| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080219074322/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14605785| archivedate= 19 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> It was announced that [[Nayantara]] would play the role of the heroine in the film, following her role opposite Ajith in ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]''.<ref name=\"nayt\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Nayan races ahead! |publisher=Sify|accessdate=24 February 2008|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609765| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080226080009/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14609765| archivedate= 26 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> In February 2008, it was confirmed that [[Navdeep]] would play a role in the film as well as [[Suman (actor)|Suman]], who will appear in a villainous role. [[Malayalam]] actor, [[Jayaram]] will also play a role in the film, which will be co-produced by actor, Arun Pandian.<ref name=\"arun\"/>\n\nNassar and [[Suhasini]] were selected to play the roles of the parents of [[Ajith Kumar|Ajith]],<ref name=\"parents\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajith's unnamed project touches French shores|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=9 February 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-01/09-02-08-ajith.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080212163942/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-01/09-02-08-ajith.html| archivedate= 12 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> whilst [[Raju Sundaram]]'s younger Brother, [[Prabhu Deva]] was given a chance to make a cameo appearance in the film as a dancer but politely refused.<ref name=\"deva\">{{cite web|year=2007|title=Prabhu Deva dances with Ajith|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=6 December 2007|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35128.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071207093549/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/35128.html| archivedate= 7 December 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref> Supporting actors [[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]], Sathyan and Sriman also play roles in ''Aegan'', as does model [[Piaa Bajpai]], who appears as the ladylove to Navdeep.<ref name=\"bas\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Billa stars in new flick|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=27 February 2008|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/feb/27billa.htm| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080301234051/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/feb/27billa.htm| archivedate= 1 March 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"piya\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Ajith Changes|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=4 April 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-08-01/aegan-04-04-08.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080407111355/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-08-01/aegan-04-04-08.html| archivedate= 7 April 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Sivakarthikeyan]] and [[Arunraja Kamaraj]] shot for the film for one day as comedians portraying spies, but following changes to the script, their roles were removed.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-10/siva-karthikeyan-values-his-20-minutes-with-ajith-ajith-siva-karthikeyan-18-02-13.html</ref> [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] was signed on as the music composer whilst [[Arjun Jena]] was the cinematographer for the project<ref name=\"parents\"/> and Milan, who did the art direction for ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]'', renews his association with Ajith in the film.<ref name=\"milan\">{{cite web|year=2008|title= Ajith's Aegan takes a cue from Billa! |publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=16 February 2008|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-02/16-02-08-aegan.html| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080221162755/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-08-02/16-02-08-aegan.html| archivedate= 21 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Aegan\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover      =\n| caption    = {{deletable image-caption|Thursday, 20 September 2018|PROD}}\n| alt        =\n| released   = 9 October 2008\n| recorded   = 2008\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 29:08\n| label      = Ayngaran Music<br />An Ak Audio<br/>[[Think Music India|Think Music]]\n| producer   = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title = [[Saroja (2008 film)#Soundtrack|Saroja]]\n| prev_year  = 2008\n| next_title = [[Silambattam (film)|Silambattam]]\n| next_year  = 2008\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack of ''Aegan'' was composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] as was the film score. It was noticeably, the third time Yuvan was scoring music for an [[Ajith Kumar]] film, after ''[[Dheena]]'' (2001) and ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]'' (2007), the songs of which had been very popular and went on to become chartbusters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/10023.html|title=Aegan \u2013 A Perfect Hat-Trick|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=5 August 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe soundtrack released on 9 October 2008,<ref name=\"musictracks\">{{cite web|author=|year=2008|title=Aegan \u2013 Official Audio Promo |publisher=[[Ayngaran International]]|accessdate=9 October 2008|url=http://www.ayngaran.com/newsdetails.php?newsid=106}}</ref> at a private ceremony at the [[Hello FM]] Studios by composer Yuvan Shankar Raja as the lead cast and the director were away shooting the video for the song in [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/2008/yuvan-aegan-audio-fm-station-131008.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120711224631/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/2008/yuvan-aegan-audio-fm-station-131008.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=11 July 2012 |title=Yuvan releases Aegan audio in FM station! |publisher=[[Oneindia]] |accessdate=5 August 2009 }}</ref> The album features 6 tracks overall, including one of the songs (\"Hey Salaa\") repeated at the end.\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra2 = [[Suvi Suresh]], Ujayinee, [[Sathyan (singer)|Sathyan]], [[Ranjith (Singer)|Ranjith]], [[Naveen]]\n| length10 = \n| total_length = 29:08\n| lyrics1 = [[Snehan]]\n| extra1 = [[Blaaze]], [[Naresh Iyer]], [[Mohammed Aslam]]\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| lyrics2 = [[Pa. Vijay]]\n| lyrics3 = Pa. Vijay\n| length9 = \n| extra3 = [[Shankar Mahadevan]]\n| lyrics4 = Snehan\n| extra4 = [[Krishna Kumar Kunnath]], [[Bela Shende]]\n| lyrics5 = Pa. Vijay\n| extra5 = [[Vasundhara Das]], [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| extra6 = \n| title10 = \n| title9 = \n| title1 = Hey Salaa\n| length4 = 4:31\n| length1 = 5:09\n| title2 = Yahoo Yahoo\n| length2 = 4:36\n| title3 = Hey Baby\n| length3 = 4:39\n| title4 = Odum Varayil\n| title5 = Kichu Kichu\n| length8 = \n| length5 = 5:11\n| title6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| lyrics6 = \n}}\n\n==Release==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Kalaignar TV|Kalaignar]]. The film was give a \"U\" certificate by the [[Indian Censor Board]], and was released during the Diwali weekend on 25 October 2008. The film was later dubbed in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Mallika I Love You''.<ref>http://www.ayngaran.com/frame.php?iframepath=newsdetails.php?newsid=1684</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n[[Sify]].com claimed that \"the trouble with the film is that it looks like an amateurish attempt by debutant director Raju Sundaram\" dismissing the [[Climax (narrative)|climax]] as \"a colossal embarrassment\", but adding that \"no film is perfect\". [[Ajith Kumar]] was praised for being \"at his best but look[ed] plump and stiff in some scenes where he need to be relaxed and natural\", drawing comparisons with a similar feedback from his previous venture, ''[[Billa (2007 film)|Billa]]''.<ref name=\"aeganreview\">{{cite web|year=2008|title=Aegan|publisher=[[Sify]].com|accessdate=2008-10-25|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14784482&ctid=5&cid=2429| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081026050553/http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14784482&ctid=5&cid=2429| archivedate= 26 October 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Nayanthara]] was said to \"look perfect as Mallika, a role that fits her like a glove\" with her make-up and costumes \"rocking\". The reviewer added that \"[[Piaa Bajpai]] is promising, Jayaram as Principal and Haneefa have been wasted and do little in the way of bringing smiles to the audiences faces\". The review also singles out the performance of rookie cinematographer, [[Arjun Jena]], whose work is labelled as \"eye-catching\".<ref name=\"aeganreview\"/>\n\nSimilarly [[Rediff]].com labelled the film as \"watchable in parts\", giving it negative feedback in comparison with ''[[Main Hoon Na]]''.<ref name=\"aeganreviewtwo\">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra|year=2008|title=Aegan is watchable in parts|publisher=[[Rediff]].com|accessdate=2008-10-25|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/oct/25aegan.htm}}</ref>  It like Sify, claims that \"Aegan loses its spontaneity and meanders between humour and seriousness\" in the second half. The reviewer praises Ajith claiming he looks as though he \"really did enjoy himself on screen, after a really long time\". The reviewer adds that \"Nayantara's outfits get smaller and smaller, while the actress herself has nothing more to do than dance in transparent saris and high-heels.<ref name=\"aeganreviewtwo\"/> Sometimes she looks amused, at others, irritated and bored\", comparing her unchallenging roles to previous roles in ''[[Sathyam (2008 film)|Sathyam]]'' and ''[[Kuselan]]''. It criticizes Piaa Bajpai claiming she \"hams it to glory\", and \"makes you want to watch [[Amrita Rao]]'s naivety in the original\", however, it praises [[Navdeep]] citing he is \"far more natural, but you pity the fact that his role is so small\". Rediff also criticized [[Suman (actor)|Suman]] and Sriman labelling their portrayals as \"pathetic\". In reference to minor characters, [[Cochin Hanifa]] is praised while [[Suhasini Mani Ratnam]]'s role is said to be \"terribly dealt with, robbing her part of any sympathy\".<ref name=\"aeganreviewtwo\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=1311638|title=Aegan}}\n\n[[Category:2008 films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:2000s action films]]\n[[Category:Tamil remakes of Hindi films]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Ooty]]\n[[Category:2000s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:2008 directorial debut films]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDevelopment:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aegan"}
{"title_page": "Abou Fadel family", "text_new": "{{Infobox family\n|name                 = Abou Fadel\n|native_name          = \u0623\u0628\u0648 \u0641\u0627\u0636\u0644\n|native_name_lang     = ar\n|other_names          = \n|religion             = Orthodox Christianity\n|type                 = <!-- Default: [[Family]]; rarely [[Royal house]], [[Noble family]], etc. See \"Types\" below. -->\n|coat_of_arms         = <!-- Coat of arms, crest, badge, emblem, banner, etc. See \"Images\" below for formatting. -->\n|coat_of_arms_size    = \n|alt                  = \n|coat_of_arms_caption = <!-- Motto/battle cry, and/or to whom and when granted, by which granting authority, etc. -->\n|image                = \n|image_size           = \n|alt2                 = \n|image_caption        = \n|parent_family        = <!-- Family (or house, clan) from which the family in subject is descended -->\n|country              = [[Lebanon]]\n|region               = [[Ain Aanoub]], [[Aley district]]\n|early_forms          = \n|etymology            = <!-- Etymology; name origin and/or meaning -->\n|origin               = [[Lebanon]]\n|founded              = 18th century\n|founder              = Sheikh Jabbour \"Abou Fadel\"\n|current_head         = \n|dissolution          = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}}, removal of public status applicable primarily to royal and aristocratic houses -->\n|deposition           = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}}, removal of authority applicable primarily to royal houses -->\n|cadet branches       = <!-- Branches families - if multiple ones, please consider using {{tlx|Template:Collapsible list}} -->\n|final_ruler          = <!-- I.e. last sovereign; applicable primarily to sovereign aristocratic dynasties -->\n|final_head           = <!-- I.e. last person with family name or else subject to end of continuous consistency -->\n|titles               = <!-- If multiple ones, please consider using {{tlx|Template:Collapsible list}} -->\n|styles               = <!-- Styles (manners of address) -->\n|members              = \n|connected_members    = <!-- Notable members in selection, only if relevant in infobox and readability-wise applicable -->\n|other_families       = <!-- Connected families, typically qualified by marriage (or rarely rivalry) -->\n|distinctions         = <!-- Primarily associated distinctions such as orders, prizes, awards, etc. -->\n|traditions           = <!-- Religion, philosophy, movement, adherence, allegiance, etc. -->\n|motto                = <!-- For non-English motto, use: ''Motto in italics'' -->\n|motto_lang           = \n|motto_trans          = \n|heirlooms            = <!-- Inheritances; antiques, mementos, jewelry, etc. -->\n|estate               = <!-- Residence, seat, etc. -->\n|website              = <!-- {{URL|example.com}}, website of the family association/foundation/memorial, etc. -->\n|footnotes            = \n}}\n\nThe '''Abou Fadel''' family (also spelled '''Abi Fadel''') is a prominent Lebanese [[Orthodox Christianity in Lebanon|Greek Orthodox Christian]] family, based in the town of [[Ain Aanoub]], in the [[Aley district]].\n\nThe surname Abou Fadel comes from Sheikh Jabbour \"Abou Fadel\", the governor of [[Ain Aanoub]] at the time, who was named Abou Fadel due to the fact that his eldest son, born in the 1700s, was named Fadel. (Abou means father in Arabic)\n\n== Origins ==\nThe family is originally from the town of [[Izra|Izraa]] in the [[Daraa Governorate]] of [[Syria]].\nIn the year 1620, Sheikh Jubra'il (grandfather of Sheikh Jabbour \"Abou Fadel\") settled in [[Ain Aanoub]], [[Lebanon]].\n\nThe Abou Fadel family descends from [[Joktan|Qahtan]], the son of [[Eber|\u02bf\u0100bir]] ([[Hud (prophet)|H\u016bd]]), an ancestor of the [[Israelites]] and the [[Ishmaelites]] according to the [[Generations of Noah|Table of Nations]] in the Book of Genesis (Genesis 10-11). [[Joktan|Qahtan]] is originally from [[Yemen]].<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/biography/Qahtan]</ref>\n[[File:Qahtanites.png|250px|thumbnail|A family tree of the Qahtanites]]\n\nThe Abou Fadel family from [[Ain Aanoub]] is not related to the Abou Fadel family of [[Brummana]].\n\n== Prominent Members of the Abou Fadel family ==\n*[[Mounir Abou Fadel]] member of the Parliament of Lebanon from 1957 to 1987, and [[Deputy speaker of the Parliament of Lebanon|Deputy Speaker of the Parliament of Lebanon]].<ref>[https://military.wikia.org/wiki/Mounir_Abou_Fadel]</ref>\n\n*[[Marwan Abou Fadel]] former MP of Mount Lebanon, Co-Founder of the [[Lebanese Democratic Party]] and Secretary General of the Lebanese Orthodox Meeting.<ref>[https://www.lorientlejour.com/article/850197/marwan-abou-fadel-nouveau-secretaire-general-de-la-rencontre-orthodoxe.html Article in ''L'orient Le Jour'']</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ain Aanoub]]\n*[[Qahtanite]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Lebanese families]]\n[[Category:Members of the Greek Orthodox Church of Antioch]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox family\n|name                 = Abou Fadel\n|native_name          = \u0623\u0628\u0648 \u0641\u0627\u0636\u0644\n|native_name_lang     = ar\n|other_names          = \n|religion             = Orthodox Christianity\n|type                 = <!-- Default: [[Family]]; rarely [[Royal house]], [[Noble family]], etc. See \"Types\" below. -->\n|coat_of_arms         = <!-- Coat of arms, crest, badge, emblem, banner, etc. See \"Images\" below for formatting. -->\n|coat_of_arms_size    = \n|alt                  = \n|coat_of_arms_caption = <!-- Motto/battle cry, and/or to whom and when granted, by which granting authority, etc. -->\n|image                = \n|image_size           = \n|alt2                 = \n|image_caption        = \n|parent_family        = <!-- Family (or house, clan) from which the family in subject is descended -->\n|country              = [[Lebanon]]\n|region               = [[Ain Aanoub]], [[Aley district]]\n|early_forms          = \n|etymology            = <!-- Etymology; name origin and/or meaning -->\n|origin  